Background

		Mr. Frederick H. Eppinger, Jr., also known as Fred, serves as Chief Executive Officer at Allmerica Property & Casualty Companies Inc. Mr. Eppinger served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of The Hanover Insurance Group, Inc. (THG) from August 2003 to June 20, 2016 and served as its Acting Chief Financial Officer from October 19, 2015 to October 30, 2015. He served as an Interim Chief Executive Officer of The Hanover Insurance Group, Inc. from September 18, ... 2007 to November, 2007. From 2001 to 2003, he served as Executive Vice President of Property & Casualty Field and Service Operations for The Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc., and served as its Director. He served as a Senior Partner in the financial institutions group at McKinsey & Company since 1992. He has more than 35 years of experience in finance and strategic marketing in the insurance industry. He joined McKinsey & Company in 1985 and worked until 2000. From 2000 to 2001, he served as Executive Vice President of Industry Services, Marketing and Service Operations of ChannelPoint, Inc. He served as Senior Vice President of Strategic Marketing for ChannelPoint, Inc. from 2000 to 2001. He has been a Director at Stewart Title Guaranty Company, Inc. since January 12, 2017. Mr. Eppinger has been a Director at Stewart Information Services Corporation since December 28, 2016. He has been a Director of Centene Corporation since April 2006. He served as a Director of The Hanover Insurance Group, Inc. since August 2003 until June 20, 2016. Mr. Eppinger holds Master's Degree in Business Administration from the Tuck School of Business at Dartmouth College in 1985 and a Bachelors of Arts degree from Holy Cross.Read Full Background




